    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix missing ho_state parameter in rrc_eNB_generate_HO_RRCConnectionReconfiguration\n\n### Summary\nThe `rrc_eNB_generate_HO_RRCConnectionReconfiguration` function was missing the `ho_state` parameter that was clearly intended to be part of its interface. This caused the function to always configure measurement events regardless of the handover state, leading to unexpected behavior during handover procedures.\n\nThe issue was identified when UE handover procedures were not behaving as expected, with measurement configurations being set up even when not needed for handover.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/RRC/LTE/rrc_proto.h`: Added missing `ho_state` parameter to function declaration\n- `openair2/RRC/LTE/rrc_eNB.c`: \n  - Added missing `ho_state` parameter to function definition\n  - Uncommented conditional code that depends on `ho_state` parameter\n  - Updated function call to include the `ho_state` parameter\n  - Fixed measurement configuration setup to only occur when `ho_state == 1`\n\n"
}